data.chText: 充满，遍布，到处都是（移动着的人、动物等）
data.enText: to be full of people, animals, etc. moving around
The streets were teeming with tourists.

ex.chText: 聚会上的食物碟满盘盈。

synonyms.bx: 指某处的某物极多，达到或近乎达到泛滥、容纳不下的程度，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 北方有许许多多野生动物。
ex.enText: Wild animals abound in the north.

synonyms.bx: 指某物大量存在，比比皆是，数量惊人，常后接介词 in/with。

ex.enText: The shops were teeming with customers.
The lake is teeming with grass carp.

ex.chText: 她的头脑里好主意极多。
ex.enText: Good ideas teem in her head.

synonyms.bx: 指某地到处都是移动着的人、动物等，也可喻指某种事物数量极多，常用于 be teeming with sth 结构中。

data.chText: 充满，遍布，到处都是（移动着的人、动物等）
data.enText: to be full of people, animals, etc. moving around
The streets were teeming with tourists.

example: people were pouring out of the theater
The garden was swarming with bees
The plaza is teeming with undercover policemen

value.def: If you say that a place is teeming with people or animals, you mean that it is crowded and the people and animals are moving around a lot.

example.ex: For most of the year, the area is teeming with tourists.
example.tran: 一年中大部分时间里，这个地区游人如织。
